en_9234393_0	Police investigations have been launched into the suspicious death of an Indian couple inside a hotel in Wellawatte.
en_9234393_1	Police Media Spokeperson ASP Ruwan Gunesekera said that the cause of the death will be traced, following the magisterial inquest into the bodies which is scheduled to be conducted today, Friday, April 3.
en_9234393_2	He also added that an investigation will also get underway to find out whether the couple had consumed poison prior to their death.
en_9234393_3	Police say that the bodies of the couple were recovered following a tip-off received on Thursday night.
en_9234393_4	The couple had arrived in the country on March 27.
